        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Fold the OpenAI-compatible chat tools, OpenAI web_search minimal, native web_search assertion, and OpenWebUI probe script tests into QA Lab native evidence paths.\n- Add QA scenario YAML entries for the folded HTTP/API proof so taxonomy coverage now fulfills `tool-invocation-api`, `openai-compatible-apis`, `reasoning-and-cache-controls`, `openai-native-web-search`, and `web-search-and-fetch`.\n- Update changed-test routing so edits to the existing Docker/client scripts run the new QA Lab evidence files.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs test/e2e/qa-lab/runtime/openai-compatible-chat-tools.e2e.test.ts test/e2e/qa-lab/runtime/openai-web-search-minimal.e2e.test.ts test/e2e/qa-lab/runtime/openai-web-search-minimal-assertions.e2e.test.ts test/e2e/qa-lab/runtime/openwebui-probe.e2e.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/scenario-catalog.test.ts test/scripts/test-projects.test.ts`\n- `node --import tsx scripts/qa-coverage-report.ts --json >/tmp/openclaw-qa-coverage-after.json`\n- `./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check --threads=1 scripts/test-projects.test-support.mjs test/scripts/test-projects.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/scenario-catalog.test.ts test/e2e/qa-lab/runtime/openai-compatible-chat-tools.e2e.test.ts test/e2e/qa-lab/runtime/openai-web-search-minimal.e2e.test.ts test/e2e/qa-lab/runtime/openai-web-search-minimal-assertions.e2e.test.ts test/e2e/qa-lab/runtime/openwebui-probe.e2e.test.ts qa/scenarios/runtime/openai-compatible-chat-tools.yaml qa/scenarios/runtime/openai-web-search-minimal.yaml qa/scenarios/runtime/openai-web-search-native-assertions.yaml qa/scenarios/runtime/openwebui-openai-compatible.yaml`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/qa-lab/src/scenario-catalog.test.ts`\n- `git diff --cached --check`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: HTTP/API script proof is now represented as QA Lab scenario evidence with primary taxonomy IDs instead